{
  "_comment": "RFC 8785 (JCS) canonicalization test vectors for PSI-Link receipts. For each vector, encoding `value` per docs/spec/CANONICAL_ENCODING.md must produce the UTF-8 byte string `bytesHex`, whose string form is `canonical` and whose SHA-256 is `sha256Hex`. Reusable by any independent implementation. See docs/spec/CANONICAL_ENCODING.md. Note: the -0 -> 0 normalization is normative (see the Numbers section and worked examples in docs/spec/CANONICAL_ENCODING.md) but cannot appear here because JSON has no negative zero -- a -0 literal parses to 0 -- so verify it from a -0 literal in your own language (the Node suite does so in packages/core/test/canonical.test.ts).",
